news.title: New York-listed KE Holdings debuts on Hong Kong stock exchange
news.para: KE's listing follows a similar move by electric vehicle manufacturer Nio Inc in March. In a listing by introduction, a company does not issue new shares or raise fresh capital, unlike a traditional initial public offering (IPO).

news.title: Sunac China misses bond coupon payment as grace period ends: Sources
news.para: Failure to make $29.5 million in interest payments on the October 2023 bond that had been due last month could represent the first offshore default on a public bond by the nation's third-largest developer by sales.

news.title: WeWork India leases 6.6 lakh sq ft space from Bhutani Group in Noida
news.para: The centre- WeWork Alphathum will be spread over an area of 6.6 lakh sq ft and will house over 8,500 desks. It is set to open in Q4 2022.

news.title: JM Financial buys two sea-view apartments in South Mumbai for Rs 60 crore
news.para: While the registration data has been suggesting more traction in housing sales in suburban localities, these luxury deals in south- and south-central Mumbai are also taking the country’s most expensive property market to new highs.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Of 2.5 lakh streelights only 15,000 'smart'
news.para: A reason could be that of the almost 2.5 lakh streetlights on main roads, societies, chawls and residential streets in the city, only 15,000 are smart, energy-saving, and low maintenance.

news.title: Kanpur development body to develop unused land of government departments
news.para: KDA vice-chairman Arvind Singh on Tuesday visited the LDA owned land measuring around one hectare situated near the KDA office at Benajhabar Road on which buildings had been constructed.

news.title: Thailand approves tax break for real estate investment trusts
news.para: Real estate investment trusts or REITs buybacks will be exempt from tax and are expected to generate re-investment of about 30 billion baht ($868.06 million) in the industry, said a government spokeswoman, Traisulee Traisoranakul.

news.title: Mumbai: Bandra building to get notice for 'inoperative' fire-fight system
news.para: "The fire-fighting system was non-operational and we will issue a notice to the building. Our investigation is still on and the exact cause of the fire is not yet known," said Hemant Parab, the chief fire officer.

news.title: Kolo raises $4 million from RTP Global and Better Capital
news.para: The new investment will help fuel its growth, enhance the consumer side product offerings including the content-recommendation engine, the community offering, digital portfolio & tools for the professionals and expand their presence across India.

news.title: Nagpur: Six-storey flat scheme built in 2005, builder wants to add floor in 2022
news.para: Constructed in 2005, Poonam Pride Condominium in Pande Layout on Khamla Road has commercial shops on upper basement and ground floor and 18 flats on six floors.

news.title: Nashik civic body to seize ACs, TVs of property tax defaulters
news.para: The cash-strapped civic body has property tax dues of over Rs 175 crore. The idea of taking such action has come from NMC administrator Ramesh Pawar, who was previously posted in Mumbai where such a measure is in place.

news.title: Lucknow development body offers 5% discount to allottees hit by pandemic
news.para: Pawan Kumar Gangwar, secretary, LDA, said, “We have a scheme under which we offer 5% discount to those allottees who have cleared 75% of their payment against the plot, apartment or house within 60 days of the purchase.

news.title: Kanpur development body razes illegal colony in Bithoor
news.para: According to a KDA representative, KDA already launched a campaign against encroachments and illegal constructions. Several private developers are selling plots without getting clearance from KDA.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to hire private agencies to complete infra in nine colonies
news.para: The nine private colonies that have received approval for takeover by the MCG include Rosewood City, Greenwood City, Malibu Town, Ardee City, Sushant Lok-2 & 3, Mayfield Garden, Vipul Gardens and Uppal Southend.

news.title: Plot sales in Haryana get a push from Haryana government
news.para: Haryana government has allowed ground coverage of 75 per cent for residential plots up 250 sq m. The current ground coverage was 66 per cent.
